main event: A civilian reported seeing a bright unidentified flying object over Columbus, Indiana on 30 November 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for a total of 4.5 minutes,The course of the object was noted as traveling from SE to NW,The report concluded that it was likely a satellite based on the review,The witness mentioned that the object appeared oval and resembled a pie plate in size,The report contained a checklist for UFO observations but no photographs were submitted.
